The paper proposes a methodology for using symbolic knowledge in deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on developing a semantic loss function for deep learning, which is a technique used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed methodology on multi-class classification and structured object prediction tasks, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
